WEBVTT

00:00:04.630 --> 00:00:09.885
Is the destiny of mankind controlled
by some transcendental entity or Law?

00:00:10.803 --> 00:00:13.764
Is it like the hand of
God hovering above?

00:00:14.890 --> 00:00:16.642
At least it is true...

00:00:17.101 --> 00:00:20.771
...that man has no
control, even over his own will.

00:00:28.529 --> 00:00:32.658
Why does Griffith value you so much?

00:00:36.078 --> 00:00:37.830
There's no reason...

00:00:38.039 --> 00:00:38.831
...in particular.

00:00:40.791 --> 00:00:43.044
Do you really need a reason...

00:00:43.669 --> 00:00:48.591
...each time I decide to
lay my life on the line for you?

00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:56.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

00:01:09.820 --> 00:01:11.906
<i>Feel no shame about shape.</i>

00:01:12.031 --> 00:01:13.824
<i>Weather changes the phrase.</i>

00:01:14.033 --> 00:01:17.536
<i>Even mother will
show you another way.</i>

00:01:17.787 --> 00:01:19.955
<i>So, put your glasses on.</i>

00:01:20.081 --> 00:01:22.041
<i>Nothing will be wrong.</i>

00:01:22.083 --> 00:01:24.210
<i>There's no blame, there's no fame.</i>

00:01:24.418 --> 00:01:26.045
<i>It's up to you.</i>

00:01:26.295 --> 00:01:29.715
<i>The first words should be found.</i>

00:01:30.341 --> 00:01:33.344
<i>Whatever holds you back.</i>

00:01:34.095 --> 00:01:34.720
<i>I...</i>

00:01:35.096 --> 00:01:35.846
<i>... can...</i>

00:01:35.930 --> 00:01:37.973
<i>I can get it off.</i>

00:01:38.182 --> 00:01:39.058
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:01:39.225 --> 00:01:39.975
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:01:40.184 --> 00:01:41.852
<i>Tell me what you want.</i>

00:01:41.977 --> 00:01:42.978
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:01:43.187 --> 00:01:43.938
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:01:44.105 --> 00:01:45.940
<i>I don't know why you are afraid.</i>

00:01:46.190 --> 00:01:47.108
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:01:47.233 --> 00:01:48.067
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:01:48.234 --> 00:01:49.735
<i>Tell me what you'd say.</i>

00:01:49.985 --> 00:01:51.070
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:01:51.237 --> 00:01:52.113
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:01:52.238 --> 00:01:52.988
<i>Too late...</i>

00:01:53.072 --> 00:01:54.573
<i>It's too late.</i>

00:01:59.620 --> 00:02:03.624
Conspiracy

00:03:38.844 --> 00:03:39.720
All right!

00:03:39.845 --> 00:03:41.513
Stretch out the rest of the ropes!

00:03:47.895 --> 00:03:49.521
Any sign of the enemy?

00:03:49.855 --> 00:03:51.232
Nothing at all.

00:03:54.485 --> 00:03:57.655
Even if hundreds or thousands
of the enemy attempt an attack...

00:03:57.780 --> 00:04:03.244
The elite of the valiant Blue Whale
Heavy Assault Knights are gathered here!

00:04:03.410 --> 00:04:07.539
No one can set one foot in
a stronghold under our guard!

00:04:13.796 --> 00:04:14.797
Listen...

00:04:15.047 --> 00:04:17.007
You always must
be on your guard in war.

00:04:17.132 --> 00:04:18.968
Do not cease to be vigilant!

00:04:19.260 --> 00:04:19.760
Yes, sir!

00:04:31.981 --> 00:04:34.483
Our commander is unusually alert.

00:04:34.608 --> 00:04:37.278
Yeah, it's because he's
been given such an important job.

00:04:37.861 --> 00:04:39.738
I suppose he cannot
help but be enthusiastic.

00:04:59.925 --> 00:05:01.051
Is it from Guts?

00:05:05.514 --> 00:05:07.933
No doubt, it's the
signal for the next phase!

00:05:08.934 --> 00:05:09.643
Good!

00:05:09.768 --> 00:05:10.436
Let's move.

00:05:44.470 --> 00:05:46.096
Enemy raid!

00:05:46.597 --> 00:05:47.306
What?

00:05:47.598 --> 00:05:48.849
An enemy raid?

00:05:48.974 --> 00:05:49.850
Enemy raid!

00:05:50.601 --> 00:05:51.226
Let's go!

00:05:51.435 --> 00:05:51.977
Ready!

00:05:53.437 --> 00:05:54.605
Enemy raid!

00:06:33.102 --> 00:06:34.770
They finally showed their faces!

00:06:35.020 --> 00:06:35.604
Ave, sir!

00:06:36.021 --> 00:06:40.025
Well, fire the cannons into
the center of their formation!

00:06:40.275 --> 00:06:43.112
Sir, it is impossible to
reach them at this distance.

00:06:43.529 --> 00:06:47.658
Then send out the whole unit,
and tear those rotten kids apart!

00:06:47.783 --> 00:06:48.283
Yes, sir!

00:06:49.368 --> 00:06:50.494
Hold on a minute!

00:06:55.165 --> 00:06:57.042
This is their trap!

00:06:58.252 --> 00:07:02.548
They must realize how difficult it
would be to destroy this stronghold.

00:07:02.673 --> 00:07:04.925
So, they are plotting to
lead us out into the field!

00:07:06.301 --> 00:07:07.678
How foolish they are!

00:07:08.011 --> 00:07:10.639
Such cheap tricks are
of no use against Sir Adon...

00:07:10.764 --> 00:07:13.308
...the most resourceful
commander in Chuder's army.

00:07:14.017 --> 00:07:15.561
Now, what are we supposed to do?

00:07:17.813 --> 00:07:19.273
Ignore them.

00:07:19.440 --> 00:07:20.315
What?

00:07:20.566 --> 00:07:22.776
Let them buzz around as they like!

00:07:43.672 --> 00:07:44.214
All right!

00:07:44.423 --> 00:07:45.841
It's time to get moving!

00:07:55.601 --> 00:07:56.852
Griffith!

00:07:57.728 --> 00:08:01.356
I've confirmed that all the
Raiders have crossed the river!

00:08:01.815 --> 00:08:02.566
Excellent!

00:08:02.733 --> 00:08:05.068
Let us vanish from
the sight of the enemy!

00:08:19.333 --> 00:08:21.752
It looks like they're pulling back!

00:08:22.127 --> 00:08:26.632
It's not worth risking their lives to
attack this impregnable stronghold!

00:09:06.421 --> 00:09:07.339
Message!

00:09:07.339 --> 00:09:08.090
Open the gate!

00:09:08.590 --> 00:09:09.424
What's happened?

00:09:09.967 --> 00:09:13.804
The General will be visiting this
castle about an important operation!

00:09:13.929 --> 00:09:15.222
R-Really?

00:09:15.472 --> 00:09:17.182
I'll pass the information
to your commander directly!

00:09:17.349 --> 00:09:18.100
Certainly!

00:09:37.619 --> 00:09:38.370
W-What's this?

00:09:50.340 --> 00:09:52.342
W-What's the meaning of this?

00:09:55.220 --> 00:09:56.888
They snuck in from the rear gate!

00:09:58.140 --> 00:10:00.350
They disappeared and
then burst in from the back!

00:10:00.475 --> 00:10:02.019
What a dirty trick!

00:10:02.519 --> 00:10:04.021
Blow them all apart!

00:10:04.146 --> 00:10:05.022
Y-Yes, sir!

00:10:05.105 --> 00:10:06.857
We'll repel them with our entire force!

00:10:11.153 --> 00:10:12.779
Should we send the signal now?

00:10:13.238 --> 00:10:15.240
No, first we secure their way in!

00:10:15.657 --> 00:10:16.783
It's an enemy raid!

00:10:17.242 --> 00:10:19.786
Bring all the bridge
guards back into the castle!

00:10:34.885 --> 00:10:35.802
Griffith...

00:10:36.011 --> 00:10:37.679
We shall wait for the signal.

00:10:37.929 --> 00:10:40.932
Can't he be quick about it?

00:10:41.558 --> 00:10:44.645
I wonder why he puts
so much faith in Guts...

00:10:45.062 --> 00:10:46.021
What's going on?

00:10:46.063 --> 00:10:47.314
Why did you open the gate?

00:10:57.699 --> 00:10:58.533
Now!

00:10:58.659 --> 00:10:59.159
Yes, sir!

00:11:01.078 --> 00:11:02.329
W-What was that?

00:11:04.081 --> 00:11:04.831
Griffith!

00:11:05.082 --> 00:11:07.584
Rush the front gate
of the castle, quickly!

00:11:44.246 --> 00:11:45.330
Shit!

00:11:45.497 --> 00:11:48.500
Do they think they can
succeed with such a small number?

00:11:51.128 --> 00:11:54.965
I, Sir Adon, shall put an
end to their lives personally!

00:12:00.887 --> 00:12:03.640
The enemy is
breaking through the front!

00:12:07.853 --> 00:12:08.729
Damn it!

00:12:08.895 --> 00:12:12.149
What sneaky tactics,
charging in from both sides like that!

00:12:50.437 --> 00:12:53.273
We're caught between the
two groups, it's out of our control!

00:12:55.776 --> 00:12:58.069
Give us your next command, sir!

00:13:02.282 --> 00:13:03.074
We retreat!

00:13:03.700 --> 00:13:04.451
But...

00:13:04.701 --> 00:13:07.454
I am one of the key
brains of the Chuder Empire!

00:13:07.579 --> 00:13:09.706
I must avoid dying in vain here!

00:13:17.964 --> 00:13:19.674
That's our commander!

00:13:19.800 --> 00:13:21.301
You had a raft prepared just in case!

00:13:21.468 --> 00:13:23.094
I am always prepared!

00:13:23.720 --> 00:13:26.306
It is a commander's duty!

00:13:26.556 --> 00:13:27.474
C-Commander!

00:13:27.682 --> 00:13:28.350
Commander!

00:13:29.226 --> 00:13:30.936
Please, take us with you.

00:13:31.228 --> 00:13:32.354
Please!

00:13:35.482 --> 00:13:36.733
Get away!

00:13:37.234 --> 00:13:39.069
How outrageous of you!

00:13:39.194 --> 00:13:40.862
This raft is a precious heirloom...

00:13:40.987 --> 00:13:43.323
...that has been handed down
through the Coborlwitz family!

00:13:43.448 --> 00:13:45.492
Remove your armor, you can all swim!

00:14:08.139 --> 00:14:09.474
You did well.

00:14:10.141 --> 00:14:12.018
I just followed your orders.

00:14:33.123 --> 00:14:34.040
We did it!

00:14:34.374 --> 00:14:37.627
Finally, we drove a
wedge into Chuder's territory.

00:14:38.128 --> 00:14:41.131
We've opened the
pass leading to Doldrey.

00:14:57.439 --> 00:15:00.191
Oh boy, that was a long walk!

00:15:00.525 --> 00:15:02.652
First I'll feed my
stomach with a sumptuous meal...

00:15:02.819 --> 00:15:04.571
...and then I'll have
a well-deserved rest!

00:15:13.788 --> 00:15:16.541
Y-Your Grace, General Boscogn!

00:15:16.791 --> 00:15:18.919
What happened to Fort Brax?

00:15:19.044 --> 00:15:22.714
W-Well, our enemy
was so devious that...

00:15:22.839 --> 00:15:27.469
...even I was inferior in
terms of underhanded trickery, sir.

00:15:27.844 --> 00:15:30.597
So, did you just roll over
and surrender the fortress?

00:15:31.181 --> 00:15:34.351
No, I deliberately withdrew and
let them occupy the fort temporarily...

00:15:34.476 --> 00:15:36.728
...to give us ample
time to regroup, sir...

00:15:37.103 --> 00:15:37.979
Enough lies!

00:15:39.105 --> 00:15:42.692
Is your brain capable of realizing how
important that fort was to our deployment?

00:15:42.817 --> 00:15:44.611
W-Well, sir...

00:15:44.736 --> 00:15:48.114
I'm warning you, this is the
last time I will support you!

00:15:48.490 --> 00:15:50.575
Lord Boscogn...

00:15:50.742 --> 00:15:53.495
A warrior must always follow
the principles of honor and justice!

00:15:53.620 --> 00:15:55.121
This is true now and always!

00:15:55.372 --> 00:15:56.081
Yes, sir!

00:16:08.093 --> 00:16:11.763
This time, I shall put an end
to them with the secret tactics...

00:16:11.888 --> 00:16:15.016
...that have been passed down through
the Coborlwitz family for 500 years!

00:16:15.100 --> 00:16:17.143
No doubt about it!

00:16:17.644 --> 00:16:19.145
It's 500 years now?

00:16:23.900 --> 00:16:26.987
Not quarreling with some evil design...

00:16:27.112 --> 00:16:29.114
Not straying from virtue...

00:16:29.406 --> 00:16:31.533
Sacrifice thyself ceaselessly...

00:16:31.658 --> 00:16:35.620
Render your services to
our fief for peace and security...

00:16:35.662 --> 00:16:38.999
The title of count is
bestowed upon thee...

00:16:39.040 --> 00:16:42.419
...place thy flesh and heart in heaven.

00:16:42.502 --> 00:16:46.297
Separate thyself from falsehood...

00:16:46.423 --> 00:16:50.677
Uphold the law, know the subjects...

00:16:51.302 --> 00:16:58.059
Be valiant, and with due
majesty, advance the war.

00:16:58.309 --> 00:17:05.108
Stand prepared for thy foe with
clue thirst for battle, and fear not.

00:17:05.483 --> 00:17:10.488
Despite the machinations of
thy foes, who march upon thee...

00:17:11.156 --> 00:17:16.786
...thou, the duly appointed count
of our glorious Kingdom of Midland...

00:17:23.668 --> 00:17:25.670
He has become a count...

00:17:26.254 --> 00:17:27.505
Say, did you hear about it?

00:17:27.630 --> 00:17:30.425
Sir Griffith was
awarded the title of count!

00:17:30.800 --> 00:17:31.926
I've heard that too!

00:17:32.010 --> 00:17:34.054
He's so handsome!

00:17:34.179 --> 00:17:38.558
I'm jealous because he is so attractive
and more graceful than any woman!

00:17:38.808 --> 00:17:39.642
Not only that...

00:17:39.768 --> 00:17:41.770
...he is the greatest
swordsman in the kingdom...

00:17:41.895 --> 00:17:43.646
...and commands the strongest army!

00:17:43.938 --> 00:17:46.066
He is far more classy
than those awkward nobles...

00:17:46.274 --> 00:17:49.194
...and he has so much
presence and elegance!

00:17:49.402 --> 00:17:56.076
True, compared to him, those
minsters in the court are all rude and rough.

00:17:56.534 --> 00:18:00.413
The poor ministers just can't
be compared with Sir Griffith!

00:18:01.081 --> 00:18:01.956
You women!

00:18:02.707 --> 00:18:04.793
You should not speak of such things!

00:18:05.085 --> 00:18:06.961
W-We are sorry, Your Excellency!

00:18:09.089 --> 00:18:10.548
Those gossips...

00:18:11.216 --> 00:18:12.926
General Yurius...

00:18:13.968 --> 00:18:19.224
What is the use of yelling at them, as
your voice may echo through the court?

00:18:25.230 --> 00:18:28.483
You look very
displeased for some reason.

00:18:28.733 --> 00:18:31.236
It makes me wonder what is wrong.

00:18:31.361 --> 00:18:32.487
It is no concern of yours!

00:18:34.864 --> 00:18:36.449
Oh, yes.

00:18:36.574 --> 00:18:40.829
Did Your Grace
happen to learn about the...

00:18:40.954 --> 00:18:44.582
...King's escort for
the upcoming Fall Hunt?

00:18:45.458 --> 00:18:46.501
In that matter...

00:18:46.626 --> 00:18:51.131
...my unit, the White Dragon Knights,
are regularly assigned to the task.

00:18:51.506 --> 00:18:53.007
What is your point?

00:18:53.383 --> 00:18:59.639
The Hawks were requested to
be the escort by Imperial decree.

00:18:59.889 --> 00:19:01.099
T-That cannot be!

00:19:01.516 --> 00:19:03.268
It is reliable information...

00:19:03.977 --> 00:19:04.769
Nonsense!

00:19:05.019 --> 00:19:07.272
The Fall Hunt is an important
event that allows the King...

00:19:07.397 --> 00:19:09.274
...to promote friendly
relations between feudal lords.

00:19:09.524 --> 00:19:12.735
Our best knights, the White
Dragons, are the only ones...

00:19:12.861 --> 00:19:16.156
...who are allowed to serve the
King in that honorable assignment.

00:19:16.281 --> 00:19:19.784
How could those upstart
thieves take that from us?

00:19:21.911 --> 00:19:24.914
What is His Majesty thinking?

00:19:25.248 --> 00:19:27.792
Will you allow this affair to take place?

00:19:27.876 --> 00:19:28.668
What do you mean?

00:19:28.918 --> 00:19:33.173
The White Dragons were reputed to
be the strongest unit in the kingdom.

00:19:33.298 --> 00:19:36.134
Nevertheless, their glory
has turned insignificant...

00:19:36.301 --> 00:19:38.428
...due to the emergence of the Hawks.

00:19:38.636 --> 00:19:40.513
Y-You...

00:19:40.805 --> 00:19:42.056
This is a rumor.

00:19:42.182 --> 00:19:44.559
As I say, it is a rumor within the court.

00:19:46.561 --> 00:19:51.941
It is an undoubted fact
that the Hawks are invincible.

00:19:52.400 --> 00:19:56.446
There is no sign that the disturbances
of war will subside any time soon.

00:19:56.946 --> 00:20:01.826
Therefore, that man will keep winning
honors through his military exploits.

00:20:02.577 --> 00:20:07.290
Additionally, His Majesty highly
appreciates that boy, as you can see.

00:20:07.415 --> 00:20:10.210
So, while I don't know how
he won His Majesty's favor...

00:20:10.418 --> 00:20:14.297
If things go badly, that
boy might become a general...

00:20:14.547 --> 00:20:15.423
Do not talk nonsense!

00:20:15.590 --> 00:20:17.175
I would never permit it!

00:20:17.300 --> 00:20:19.844
It is unheard of, some upstart
mercenary becoming a general!

00:20:20.345 --> 00:20:24.224
That bastard could
be a general like I am?

00:20:25.808 --> 00:20:31.314
That man of common origins
would be on the same level as me?

00:20:31.439 --> 00:20:35.610
Well, I just mentioned the
possibility, that which could be...

00:20:35.693 --> 00:20:36.611
I won't allow it!

00:20:37.570 --> 00:20:39.614
I absolutely will not allow it!

00:20:42.700 --> 00:20:45.828
However, some danger
always lies in the act of hunting...

00:20:45.954 --> 00:20:48.081
...despite the fact
it is an Imperial event.

00:20:49.999 --> 00:20:55.505
You never know what kind of
beasts hide within the woods...

00:20:56.256 --> 00:20:57.632
What are you trying to say?

00:20:57.757 --> 00:20:59.968
Of course, not only
are the beasts dangerous...

00:21:00.009 --> 00:21:04.138
...but also the stray arrows that
may have been launched at the beasts.

00:21:04.639 --> 00:21:05.765
A stray arrow?

00:21:07.267 --> 00:21:11.896
And a nastily
poisoned stray arrow at that...

00:21:13.898 --> 00:21:15.858
If you mean...

00:21:16.526 --> 00:21:18.987
A stray arrow, General.

00:21:29.038 --> 00:21:30.290
A stray arrow...

00:21:30.623 --> 00:21:31.749
Interesting!

00:21:32.917 --> 00:21:36.254
It would be a proper death
for a man of common birth!

00:22:02.905 --> 00:22:05.033
<i>Looking back, the morning comes.</i>

00:22:05.199 --> 00:22:08.703
<i>Don't find your face in your glass.</i>

00:22:09.954 --> 00:22:12.707
<i>Take the moonlight by the tail.</i>

00:22:12.832 --> 00:22:15.710
<i>It's a rainy sight that you're shading.</i>

00:22:17.420 --> 00:22:18.963
<i>What is that?</i>

00:22:19.088 --> 00:22:20.214
<i>It's just the same.</i>

00:22:20.340 --> 00:22:23.426
<i>What is trying on your crown?</i>

00:22:24.677 --> 00:22:27.597
<i>I'm spending my
glass and walking back.</i>

00:22:27.680 --> 00:22:30.933
<i>So wear my glass, you're fading.</i>

00:22:31.225 --> 00:22:34.562
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:34.979 --> 00:22:37.857
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:38.608 --> 00:22:41.611
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:42.487 --> 00:22:45.239
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:46.240 --> 00:22:49.118
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:49.994 --> 00:22:51.829
<i>I'm waiting...</i>

00:23:06.886 --> 00:23:08.888
Next Episode

00:23:10.098 --> 00:23:15.019
Nothing is more profound or
ever-lasting than envy and enmity.

00:23:16.521 --> 00:23:22.110
Man lives on in the deep
darkness of such feelings...

00:23:22.360 --> 00:23:28.282
...and there, he forever
strives against his sinful fate.

00:23:28.908 --> 00:23:32.120
In this world, is having
affection for another an avoidable sin?

00:23:33.913 --> 00:23:36.916
Assassination

00:23:37.305 --> 00:24:37.292
